  "body": "## What's Changed\r\n* chore: enable build_layers.sh to build from specific dd-trace-py commit by @joeyzhao2018 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/734\r\n* ci: add test optimization reporting for system-tests by @nccatoni in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/735\r\n* Add span.kind=server to aws.lambda spans by @jchrostek-dd in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/745\r\n* fix(cold_start): capture trace context before finishing spans by @jchrostek-dd in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/746\r\n* ci: skip ddtrace 4.6.* version by @brettlangdon in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/750\r\n* ci: adding schedule to system-tests workflow by @nccatoni in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/744\r\n* ci: install dd-trace-py pipeline wheels when run as child pipeline by @brettlangdon in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/749\r\n* feat: slim down the zip ddtrace package by @juanjux in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/753\r\n* fix: disable Client Side Stats by default by @ojproductions in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/756\r\n* feat: add durable_function_execution_status tag to aws.lambda span by @jchrostek-dd in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/751\r\n* tiny increase of lambda layer size limit by @emmettbutler in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/760\r\n* chore: remove ddtrace patch.py files from layer by @brettlangdon in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/763\r\n* feat: [SVLS-8493] rename durable function tags to use aws_lambda prefix by @lym953 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/757\r\n* ci: fix ddtrace version detection by @brettlangdon in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/764\r\n* chore: remove all ddtrace ci viz paths from layer by @brettlangdon in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/765\r\n* ci: migrate CI secrets from AWS SSM to Vault KV by @duncanista in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/766\r\n* use serverless-specific wheel in layer by @emmettbutler in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/762\r\n* more complete backward compatibility by @emmettbutler in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/775\r\n* ci: revert PRs #762 and #775 by @brettlangdon in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/776\r\n* feat: [SVLS-8720] Add span tag aws_lambda.durable_function.first_invocation by @lym953 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/747\r\n* fix: remove return from finally block to resolve Python 3.14 SyntaxWa… by @jcstorms1 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/767\r\n* Add ability to use ddtrace_serverless wheels in layer build by @emmettbutler in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/777\r\n* Revert \"fix: remove return from finally block to resolve Python 3.14 SyntaxWa…\" by @rithikanarayan in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/780\r\n* handle any preceding directory name by @emmettbutler in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/778\r\n* fix: negative duration on aws.apigateway.authorizer span by @pablomartinezbernardo in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/782\r\n* fix: remove return from finally block to resolve Python 3.14 SyntaxWarning by @rithikanarayan in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/783\r\n* Migrate e2e status to short-lived token by @rithikanarayan in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/784\r\n* Remove unused ddtrace appsec packages by @avara1986 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/761\r\n* fix: Bump ujson minimum version to 5.10.0 by @joeyzhao2018 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/787\r\n* Update integration test snapshots by @rithikanarayan in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/792\r\n* fix: disable remote configuration by default in Lambda by @zarirhamza in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/797\r\n* [SVLS-8580] fix: correct durable execution statuses to match Python SDK InvocationStatus enum by @lym953 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/793\r\n* bump vulnerable dependencies  by @ojproductions in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/796\r\n* v8.124.0 by @ojproductions in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/798\r\n\r\n\r\n>[!IMPORTANT]\r\n> For Python 3.8 and 3.9: `dd-trace-py` version is [v3.19.6](https://github.com/DataDog/dd-trace-py/releases/tag/v3.19.6)\r\n> For Python >= 3.10: `dd-trace-py` version is [v4.7.1](https://github.com/DataDog/dd-trace-py/releases/tag/v4.7.1)\r\n\r\n\r\n>[!IMPORTANT]\r\n> This layer is currently unavailable in aws region `me-south-1`, due to ongoing incidents in the area's infrastructure\r\n\r\n```\r\n# AWS Commercial\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python38:123\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python38-ARM:123\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python39:123\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python39-ARM:123\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python310:123\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python310-ARM:123\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python311:123\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python311-ARM:123\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python312:123\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python312-ARM:123\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python313:123\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python313-ARM:123\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python314:123\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python314-ARM:123\r\n\r\n# AWS GovCloud\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:002406178527:layer:Datadog-Python38:123\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:002406178527:layer:Datadog-Python38-ARM:123\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:002406178527:layer:Datadog-Python39:123\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:002406178527:layer:Datadog-Python39-ARM:123\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:002406178527:layer:Datadog-Python310:123\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:002406178527:layer:Datadog-Python310-ARM:123\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:002406178527:layer:Datadog-Python311:123\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:002406178527:layer:Datadog-Python311-ARM:123\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:002406178527:layer:Datadog-Python312:123\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:002406178527:layer:Datadog-Python312-ARM:123\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:002406178527:layer:Datadog-Python313:123\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:002406178527:layer:Datadog-Python313-ARM:123\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:002406178527:layer:Datadog-Python314:123\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:002406178527:layer:Datadog-Python314-ARM:123\r\n```\r\n## New Contributors\r\n* @jchrostek-dd made their first contribution in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/745\r\n* @juanjux made their first contribution in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/753\r\n* @ojproductions made their first contribution in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/756\r\n* @emmettbutler made their first contribution in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/760\r\n* @pablomartinezbernardo made their first contribution in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/782\r\n\r\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/compare/v8.123.0...v8.124.0",
